## Roadmap

- Fix the static date range using a dynamic relative date filter to achieve real-time monthly updates without manual refresh
- Fix the single-state geographic view using a drill-down hierarchy from state to city to achieve more granular regional insight
- Fix the manual return rate calculation using a parameter-driven threshold to achieve flexible "high risk" categorization that stakeholders can adjust themselves
- Fix the lack of customer segmentation using RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) analysis to achieve a clearer view of which customer segments drive the most returns

---

## 🎯 Business Problem

> *What is causing high return rates, and what can leadership do about it?*

Returns are costly. This analysis surfaces which products, customers, categories, and regions are driving returns — so decision-makers can act with confidence.

